The paper deals with the problem of learning parameters of a mixture of Mallows models, which is a popular generative model for ranking data. This problem falls under the domain of machine learning and statistics, and hence the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of determinantal identities and information-theoretic lower bounds, which are techniques used in the areas of discrete mathematics and information theory, respectively. Therefore, cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications in social choice, recommendation systems, and natural language processing, which are areas of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social informatics (cs.SI).
